1 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, the study must include an examination of the regulation of
2 water, wetlands, and inundated lands laws of other states; an inventory of all federal, state, and
3 local laws, regulations, and policies relating to the jurisdiction of water and wetlands; an
4 analysis of the environmental protection and public health jurisdictional framework, including an
5 identification of potential conflicts, overlaps, and gaps in authority; and recommendations for
6 improving the clarity, consistency, and efficiency of the jurisdictional framework in water
7 management; and
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Legislative Management report its findings and
9 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
10 the Seventieth Legislative Assembly.
